                            Osmedeus Next Generation v5.0.2 by @j3ssie

                            A Modern Orchestration Engine for Security

                                            ¯\_(ツ)_/¯

◆ Description
  Osmedeus is a powerful workflow engine for executing automated
  reconnaissance and security assessment workflows.

  It supports both module (single execution units) and flow (multi-module
  orchestration) workflows with parallel and sequential execution patterns.

▶ Key Features
  • Execute YAML-defined security workflows
  • Support for parallel and sequential execution
  • Distributed scanning with master/worker architecture
  • Template variables and utility functions

▷ Quick Start
  # Run a module workflow
  osmedeus run -m simple-module -t example.com

  # Run a flow workflow
  osmedeus run -f recon-workflow -t example.com

  # Evaluate a utility function
  osmedeus func e 'log_info("Hello {{target}}")' -t example.com

  # List available workflows
  osmedeus workflow list

  # Show all usage examples
  osmedeus --usage-example

📖 Documentation: https://docs.osmedeus.org

Usage:
  osmedeus [flags]
  osmedeus [command]

Available Commands:
  agent       Run an ACP agent interactively
  assets      Query and list discovered assets
  client      Interact with a remote osmedeus server
  cloud       Cloud infrastructure management commands
  completion  Generate the autocompletion script for the specified shell
  config      Manage osmedeus configuration
  db          Database management commands
  eval        Evaluate a script (shorthand for 'func eval')
  function    Execute and test utility functions
  health      Check and fix environment health (alias for 'osmedeus install validate')
  help        Help about any command
  install     Install workflows, base folder, or binaries
  query       Query scan data (agent-friendly)
  run         Execute a workflow
  scan        Execute a workflow (alias for 'run')
  serve       Start the Osmedeus web server
  snapshot    Export and import workspace snapshots
  uninstall   Remove Osmedeus installation (base folder, workspaces, and binary)
  update      Update osmedeus to the latest version
  version     Print version information
  worker      Worker node commands for distributed scanning
  workflow    Manage workflows

Flags:
  -b, --base-folder string       base folder containing workflows and settings (default is $HOME/osmedeus-base/)
      --ci-output-format         output results in JSON format for CI pipelines
      --debug                    enable debug mode (verbose + debug logging)
      --disable-color            disable colored output
      --disable-db               disable database connection (warning: some features unavailable)
      --disable-logging          disable all logging output
      --disable-notification     disable all notifications
      --force                    skip confirmation prompts and force operations
      --full-usage-example       show full usage with all flags in pager mode
  -h, --help                     help for osmedeus
      --json                     output in JSON format
      --log-file string          path to log file (logs to both console and file)
      --log-file-tmp             create temporary log file osmedeus-log-<timestamp>.log
      --settings-file string     settings file path (default is $HOME/osmedeus-base/osm-settings.yaml)
  -q, --silent                   silent mode - suppress all output except errors
      --skip-auto-setup          skip automatic first-time setup
      --spinner                  show spinner animations during execution
  -H, --usage-example            show comprehensive usage examples for all commands
  -v, --verbose                  enable verbose output
      --version                  version for osmedeus
      --width int                max table width for display (0 = auto-detect terminal width)
  -F, --workflow-folder string   custom workflow folder (default is $HOME/osmedeus-base/workflows/)

Use "osmedeus [command] --help" for more information about a command.
